 Its reasons are as follows: From my self‑introduction I prefer high‑energy, guitar‑forward rock with crunchy, midrange‑heavy lead tones, bluesy riffs, punchy analog warmth and a propulsive groove; I also value grit, dynamic contrast, visceral presence, clear stereo separation, discernible overdubs and tight vocal parts when they serve the song. I explicitly dislike overly sterile, adult‑contemporary production: smoothed, multi‑tracked vocals, heavy gated reverb, soft‑compressed dynamics, and homogenized mastering that drain energy and guitar bite.
